                        owder of Diatrion Pipereon, a Dram and half; aromatic Oyl of Sugar, two Drams. Make a Coarſe Powder.

THE Blood that is evacuated by ſpitting, may either proceed from the Stomac, (of which elſewhere) or from the Palat, Noſtrils, and Gums, as was related in the laſt Article; or from the Organs of Reſpiration, viz. the Windpipe, Bronchia or Lungs; in which caſe, the Diſeaſe is called (
                              〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                           ) Hemoptyſis, or a ſpitting of Blood, and is the ſubject of this Paragraph. The general Cauſes are already accounted for: The particular Cauſes are,
